   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>L. Not Speaking against the Brothers</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>by Keeping the Law</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>James told us not to speak against the brothers by keeping the law 4:11-12 .</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>But Paul said that he lived no longer to the law and that he was not in debt to the law Rom 7:6; Gal 2:19 .</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>M. Confiding Not in Self-will but in the Lord</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>We should confide not in our self-will but in the Lord James 4:13-17 .</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>This can only be carried out by the new man.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>N. Awaiting the Lord's Coming</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>with Long-suffering</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>James exhorted us to await the Lord's coming with long-suffering 5:7-9 .</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>O. Taking the Prophets and Job as Examples</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>in Suffering Evil with Endurance</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>James also told us to take the prophets and Job as examples in suffering evil with endurance 5:10-11 .</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>But at Job's time there was no new man.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Here we can see the mixture in James.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>P. Speaking Honestly without Swearing</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>James 5:12 tells us to speak honestly without swearing.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Q. Praying according to the Example of Elijah</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>James 5:13-18 speaks of praying according to the example of Elijah.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>R. Turning Back the Brother</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>Led Astray from the Truth</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Finally, James tells us to turn back the brother led astray from the truth 5:19-20 .</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>All of the above items are the virtues of Christian perfection stressed by James.</S>
   </TEXT>
